    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In Scotland, a pair of straps or pieces of string tied around the leg just below the knee to secure the trousers of farmworkers; used to keep the bottom of trousers lifted clear of dirt to keep them clean.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Justo debajo de la rodilla para asegurar los pantalones de los granjeros. Usada para mantener la parte inferior de los pantalones libre de la suciedad y para mantener las piernas limpias.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
